IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: On 6/12/23, at JFK International Airport CBP officers were inspecting a shipment-inbound from China. Upon examination of a brown box wrapped in yellow tape, manifested as anti-theft equipment,. Officers found 6 foil packages with an off-white, crystalline substance. Officers tested the substance onsite using the Gemini Thermo-Scientific Device. The result was positive for N, N-DIMETHYLPENTYLONE HYDROCHLORIDE, a Schedule I Narcotic. A total of 6.0kg was seized. On 6/28/23 the parcel was retrieved from HSI, located in Baltimore Maryland by members of the Metropolitan Area Drug Task Force and stored. On 7/3/23 the parcels contents were transported to the MSP Forensics Lab in Pikesville for analysis and the crystalline substance again returned positive. The shipments displayed the following information (written below as shown on the labels): FROM: JUSDA SUPPLY CHAIN MANAGEMENT 0000000000 JUSDA SUPPLY CHAIN MANAGEMENT 14808 GUY R BREWER BLVD JAMAICA NY 11434 TO: THOMAS WALLACE 2453452145 THOMAS WALLACE 10200 JUNIPER DR BOWIE MD 20721 Through investigative means a suspect by the name of Brandon Columbus Wallace (B/M, DOB: 12/9/94) was developed. Wallace possessed an extensive CDS violation background.During the week of 6/30/23 till the time of the controlled delivery visual surveillance at various times of day were conducted on the target address in Bowie. At no time was B.C. Wallace observed at the residence. On 7/7/23 the MADTF attempted a controlled delivery and parcel was refused by a subject that answered the door. The address has been flagged for future CDS investigations. CASE SUSPENDED
